      <Placemark>
        <name>THE BACKPACK SHACK</name>
        <description><![CDATA[STREET ADDRESS: Alhof Drive, Fairview, Mossel Bay, 6506, Western Cape, South Africa<br><br>GPS COORDINATES:-34.17401, 22.11633<br><br>PHONE: +27446930050<br><br>WHATSAPP: +27 72 625 5893<br><br>EMAIL: Not clearly listed publicly — enquiries are typically handled via the parent property (Hotel Portão Diaz) or booking platform messaging.<br><br>WEBSITE: No dedicated standalone official website — current information and bookings are hosted via the parent property and aggregator sites such as Hotelonia (https://thebackpackshack.hotelonia.com/)<br><br>SOCIAL MEDIA: Facebook: www.facebook.com/backpackshackmosselbay/ (Active page for The Backpack Shack)<br><br>BOOKING PLATFORM URLS: Booking.com: www.booking.com/hotel/za/the-backpack-shack.html<br><br>SafariNow: www.safarinow.com/go/hotel-portao-diaz/ (Backpack Shack units are listed under this parent property)<br><br>Agoda: www.agoda.com/the-backpack-shack-hostel/hotel/mossel-bay-za.html<br><br>GOOGLE RATING: ~4.1 / 5 stars (Based on public reviews for "The Backpack Shack")<br><br>BOOKING.COM RATING: 7.0 / 10 (Rated "Good" based on verified guest stays)<br><br>ACCOMMODATION TYPE: Budget Backpackers & Hostel (Mixed Dormitories and Private "Design" Rooms; operates as the budget-friendly annex of the adjacent Hotel Portão Diaz)<br><br>PRICE RANGE: Budget. ~R300 for dorm beds up to ~R950–R1,100 for private "Design" rooms (rates vary by season and specific unit type).<br><br>VIBE-METER: 60% Laid-back Garden Retreat / 40% Local Urban Explorer Hub — a unique blend of traditional backpacker culture situated within a local residential suburb, offering a more "authentic" South African feel than the main tourist strip.<br><br>DECIBEL LEVEL: Moderate — while the garden is tranquil, the presence of an on-site bar, karaoke facilities, and a small casino can lead to livelier evenings, particularly on weekends.<br><br>SOLO-FEMALE-FRIENDLINESS SCORECARD: 3 / 5. The property is secure with a 24-hour front desk, but its location in the D'Almeida/Fairview area is a few kilometres from the central tourist hub; solo travellers should use taxis or shuttles for transport at night.<br><br>SAFETY RATING: Yellow. Located in a residential suburb with 24/7 security and secure parking on-site. It is generally safe within the property, though standard urban awareness is required when walking in the surrounding neighbourhood.<br><br>KEY AMENITIES:<br>Outdoor swimming pool and sun terrace<br>On-site restaurant serving traditional African cuisine<br>Fully licensed bar and lounge area<br>Free Wi-Fi in public areas and rooms<br>Communal kitchen and outdoor braai (barbecue) facilities<br>24-hour front desk and security<br>On-site casino and karaoke entertainment<br>Free private parking and airport shuttle service (surcharge)<br><br>NEARBY HIGHLIGHTS:<br>Diaz Beach & Santos Beach (~5-minute drive / 1.8 km)<br><br>Botlierskop Private Game Reserve (~14-minute walk / 1.2 km)<br><br>Bartolomeu Dias Museum Complex (Historical "Post Office Tree")<br><br>Mossel Bay Golf Club (Championship course nearby)<br><br>St. Blaize Lighthouse & Hiking Trail<br><br>MANAGEMENT STYLE: Efficient and hospitable. As a satellite property of Hotel Portão Diaz, management is professional with a structured 24-hour reception service. The staff are noted for their local knowledge and help with booking regional tours (shark diving, whale watching, etc.), though the service style is more functional-hotel than intimate-hostel.<br><br>EMPLOYMENT ETHICS: There is no verifiable evidence of a formal volunteer exchange programme (e.g., Workaway or Worldpackers). The establishment appears to rely on standard paid local staff for its hospitality, maintenance, and security operations.<br><br>THE BLURB:<br>The Backpack Shack offers a distinctive departure from the standard "surfer hostel" aesthetic typically found along the Garden Route. Tucked away in the residential suburb of Fairview/D'Almeida, it provides an "upcycled township" feel, utilizing materials like demolition wood and corrugated iron to create a vibrant, eco-conscious atmosphere. Operating as the budget-friendly sister to the well-known Hotel Portão Diaz, guests here enjoy the bes]]></description>
